samurai
------------------------------------------
samurai is a ninja-compatible build tool written in C99 with a focus on
simplicity, speed, and portability.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.3.0-3
  make-4.2.1-2
  ninja-1.8.2-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/michaelforney/samurai

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/michaelforney/samurai/archive/0.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack samurai-0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./samurai-0.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/samurai-0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/samurai-0.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(samurai)
  /usr/bin/samu.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/samurai.README
  /usr/share/doc/samurai/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/samurai/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/samu.1.gz

------------------

